o high school. This book examines the key attributes of successful dual language programs, as well as the challenges and opportunities involved in extending the dual language instructional model to pre-K and secondary settings. Chapter authors, who are themselves both researchers and practitioners, explore the latest research and policy implications for implementation of dual language in three different contexts; within a school, a dual language school and a dual language district. This book will be of interest to teachers, teacher educators, professional development specialists, policymakers, administrators, and researchers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aEducation, BilingualvCase studies. 0aEducation, BilingualzUnited StatesvCase studies. 0aEducation, BilingualzUnited States. 0aEducation, Bilingual. 0aMulticultural educationvCase studies. 0aMulticultural educationzUnited StatesvCase studies. 0aMulticultural educationzUnited States. 0aMulticultural education. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aBilingual .  aDual Language Programs.  aDual Language research and policy.  aDual Language.  aLanguage Education.  aLanguage Learning.  aLanguage Policy.  abilingualism.1 aArias, M. Beatriz, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aArteagoitia, Igone, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeatriz, M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChristian, Donna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFee, Molly, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aG.Wiley, Terrence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcía, Ofelia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGenesee, Fred,